In June, the Commission published the results of the public consultation which proposed the inclusion of the Welsh Parliament and which received broad support.
As regards the addresses of Members, the Commission prefers the Welsh Parliament Member (representative of the Welsh Parliament) and its abbreviation WMP, but the public consultation favoured the MWP alternative.
Members come up with new alternatives, but the agreement is rather cumbersome, which is a problem for the President of the National Assembly, Elin Jones, who will have to submit a bill on change of name in the coming weeks.
