Red Dag News: Concentrating in Pinellas, Manatee and Sarasota
The latest report by the Florida Fish and Animal Commission shows a general reduction in redfish concentrations in some areas of Tampa Bay.
According to the FWC, there have been more speckling blooms in the provinces of Pinellas, Manatee, Sarasota, Charlotte and Collier, suggesting a decrease in concentration.
The extent of the red tide is about 130 miles of coastline, from the northern Pinellas to the southern Lee counties.
There are spots about 10 miles outside Hillsborough County, but compared to last week, there are relatively smaller areas.
The red tide was also observed in Pasco County.
Last week, a medium concentration was reported in Pinellas County and along its coasts, a low to high concentration in Hillsborough County along the coast, a background to high concentration in Manatee County, a background to high concentration in Sarasota County and its coasts, a background to medium concentration in Charlotte County, a background to high concentration in Lee County and its coasts and a low concentration in Collier County.
There were still reports of respiratory irritation in the departments of Pinellas, Manatee, Sarasota, Lee and Collier.
Last week, there were no reports of respiratory irritation from northwest Florida.
